Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    # Update package lists and install Python + pip
    apt-get update && \
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip && \
    apt-get clean && \
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

    # Install pytest for the checker suite
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Prepare initial exercise data
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Create the required directory structure
    mkdir -p /home/user/forensics

    # Make the forensics directory writable by non-root users so that the
    # student can create cron_audit.log later.
    chmod 0777 /home/user/forensics

    # Populate the compromised crontab file with the exact contents
    printf '*/5 * * * * /home/user/scripts/backup.sh\n0 3 * * * /home/user/scripts/cleanup.sh\n@reboot /home/user/scripts/bitcoin_miner.sh\n' \
        > /home/user/forensics/compromised.cron

    # Ensure correct permissions on the crontab file (world-readable, not writable)
    chmod 0644 /home/user/forensics/compromised.cron

%labels
    chmod 755 /home/user

    Author          example
    Description     "Environment for compromised crontab forensic analysis exercise"

%help
This Apptainer image sets up the initial filesystem state for the
“compromised crontab” incident-response task and includes pytest so that
automated tests can validate both the initial and final states.